  "prompt": "What does \"last activity\" mean on Skype?",
  "response": "On Skype, \"last activity\" typically refers to the most recent time a contact or participant was active on the platform. This could include actions such as sending a message, making a call, or any other interaction that indicates the user was using Skype. It provides an indication of when a person was last online and available to communicate. This information can help you gauge whether someone is likely to see a message soon or if they might be inactive for a while. Keep in mind that privacy settings can sometimes affect whether this status is visible to others.",
